<node id="JZ">
  <data key="d0">JZ</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">JZ is the set of initials identifying the presiding judge or judicial officer assigned to the federal legal case designated as 3:22-cv-01342-JZ. These initials are integrated into the formal case identifier, docket number, and document headers to designate the specific individual responsible for the judicial oversight and management of the litigation. Within this jurisdiction and legal context, the initials JZ are specifically identified as representing Judge Jack Zouhary.

As the presiding authority for Case 3:22-cv-01342-JZ, Judge Jack Zouhary is the judicial official tasked with overseeing the proceedings and managing the administration of the court record. The inclusion of these initials in the case number provides essential clarity for court administration and legal citations, ensuring that the assigned judge is easily identifiable throughout the lifecycle of the litigation.</data>
