<node id="Text Messages">
  <data key="d0">Text Messages</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Text Messages are digital and electronic communications utilized as a primary medium for documenting and relaying coal delivery requirements, as well as performance grievances. In a business context, these messages serve to support and record oral requirements for coal transactions, providing a formal log of operational communication. Throughout the legal proceedings and transcript segments, they are frequently referred to using terms such as "text," "texted," or "texts," and function as critical evidence or subject matter within the case.

As part of the ongoing litigation, Text Messages have been formally requested for production and entered into the record across a wide range of exhibits. Specifically, these electronic communication logs are identified as Exhibits 10, 27, 31, 38, 39, 40, 41, 57, 58, 62, and 84 within the exhibit index. These exhibits serve as a comprehensive record of the digital interactions relevant to the dispute.

In the context of witness testimony, Text Messages represent the primary electronic records about which the witness is questioned, particularly at the outset of transcript segments. By serving as documented evidence, these messages help clarify the requirements and performance standards discussed between the parties involved in the coal delivery process.</data>
