<node id="Michael Wagner">
  <data key="d0">Michael Wagner</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Michael Wagner is a management-level employee based in Houston who specializes in raw material procurement and contract administration. Mentored by Tom Reed, Wagner took on significant responsibilities regarding the documentation and oversight of coal procurement efforts. His role involved managing high-level business communications and ensuring that contract requirements, payments, and shipments were handled according to organizational standards.

In his professional dealings with the entity Fire Star, Michael Wagner maintained a complex communication dynamic. He authored correspondence congratulating connections at Fire Star and claimed to have engaged in direct dialogue with the company, yet he also reportedly experienced periods of difficulty in receiving responses from them. Wagner’s oversight extended to operational quality control; he once directed Fire Star to suspend coal deliveries for a specific duration due to identified quality problems.

Michael Wagner also acted as a directive figure for other personnel and witnesses involved in these business processes. He provided instructions to facilitate or cease communications with external parties such as Fire Star and an individual identified as Dwayne (or Duane). His coordination efforts were conducted through various mediums, including telephone calls regarding security and documentation matters and text message exchanges with Duane concerning the specifics of coal shipments and financial payments.</data>
