<node id="Albion">
  <data key="d0">Albion</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Albion is an industrial plant location and operational ACC facility that plays a significant role in coal usage and distribution networks. As an operational site, Albion lacks internal coal grinding capabilities and is consequently dependent on external processing to meet its energy needs. It primarily relies on the Archbold facility to provide its coal requirements in powdered form, consuming approximately 35 tons of processed coal daily. While the facility is generally described as being entirely dependent on the Archbold plant for regular supplies, some documentation characterizes these requirements as being occasionally supplied through that location. Furthermore, Albion serves as a destination for various work-in-progress ingredients transferred from the Archbold site.

In a broader logistical and contractual context, Albion is identified as a primary destination for bulk shipments and various coal blends. The facility’s material needs were explicitly contemplated in a coal supply agreement between ACC and Fire Star, and the plant was actively supplied under this contract throughout 2021. Because of its operational structure, the specific usage data for Albion is typically integrated into the reporting for the Archbold site. Albion is frequently mentioned alongside other locations, such as Belvidere and Troy, particularly in the context of operational issues and the necessity of ensuring material needs are covered.

Beyond its physical operations, Albion is recognized as a business entity involved in specific financial accounts and corporate reporting. It is extensively referenced within the index of legal transcripts and associated with various corporate documents, including a specific tab within an Excel file labeled as Defendant's Exhibit 4. As a key node in the logistics chain for coal distribution, the role of Albion encompasses both physical consumption and administrative significance within its corporate and legal framework.&lt;SEP&gt;A location or proper name referenced in the legal transcript index on page 36.&lt;SEP&gt;Albion is a plant location mentioned by Mr. Miller as requiring a supply of ground coal.&lt;SEP&gt;Albion is an entity or term appearing in the transcript index at line 139:6.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3e53329a256cc082bedeaabb7ee866bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-72864d43546b0fdb0889bb6341c0c099&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00c571593b1228b7b76059ab51abd6c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1acc0c2748bf5b184c2f1284638c9089&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-106b16a32678dd2303338174088c2dfa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbd2c15dff71dc080694d39bcb9aee57&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-254a838d380639a750a841f49783616f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d6d709d0ec6b3472961b88797a09fc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e412217ddf7b2fe6ee24bebcb8abb8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c8243480b3587c15b506c6f565ce13b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-890fa85548914bc59a26974a429c4e21&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a84012ee527927df3cba96bd82645063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0fac00b24251700d101d62ba241bf375&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf5bccaff8fd537a70e39101e74dafe1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6651d4b1167389e3589940fb1cba165&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63ca2f57c8ad6dbfaa5a4f3ea01f9700&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff296c565c3f4e80b9959ae67262e606&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76b142c69bd1fd0042f02d144521dea3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce0536f5d7fd6c2825c2025e7a85ff94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d265c5065bea7006d9e21d1c75d8eb5b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea0c3d9ff35641a8bb5a123cadebd49d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c49f929503157c8fd745523af065f8b</data>
