<node id="Dwayne">
  <data key="d0">Dwayne</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Dwayne is a central figure in coal supply and logistics, primarily recognized for his extensive involvement in the energy sector as a representative and account manager for Fire Star. Associated with the Joneses and the broader organization referred to as Energy, he serves as the primary contact for coal supply agreements, possessing the significant authority to either approve or halt coal sales from Fire Star. His professional identity is linked to the email address DNRJones@AOL.com. In addition to his management roles, he is identified as a supervisor or employer of Dwayne Cotton, with whom he maintains a close business association.

Within his operational capacity, Dwayne coordinates delivery requirements, manages volume forecasts, and adjusts orders in response to mechanical failures or changing facility needs. He receives information from Neil Miller regarding the number of loads that ACC can accept weekly and has been the recipient of communications from Miller concerning broader coal supply issues. Beyond his administrative duties, Dwayne owns a fleet of trucks and manages coal shipments, exercising direct authority over logistics and the deployment of his transportation equipment. His professional interactions involved frequent emails and telephone calls—including a notable business call on March 8, 2022—to address tonnage requirements, payments, and delivery logistics.

Dwayne’s professional standing is characterized by significant conflicts and extensive legal scrutiny. He is mentioned prominently throughout legal proceedings and indexes, with numerous references recorded between pages 4 and 161 of the case documentation, occasionally appearing in close proximity to the name "Duane." He was involved in a heated professional rift with an individual named Michael and the company ACC over unpaid invoices and coal quality disputes. These management frictions led Dwayne to at times restrict the use of his truck fleet for coal transportation. Due to these ongoing legal and internal conflicts, direct communication with Dwayne was eventually ceased by certain parties in March 2022.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3e53329a256cc082bedeaabb7ee866bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3aa6b92318a7dbc503df2e6bc0457f59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b14692172e18d355177e1f52adca6616&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-72864d43546b0fdb0889bb6341c0c099&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-239b957363afa06896c850b0b3096cab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5615da5f26bf1a4c451ff93c5d9cf990&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20985475deeff0feffae4d18b011ee8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1acc0c2748bf5b184c2f1284638c9089&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-106b16a32678dd2303338174088c2dfa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa66b57078d2cf7712dd3f3924568ac6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea56e06fa48990cb993a7e9f44e99a73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3cf9a12f8ab261dacc4fe581a64518c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbd2c15dff71dc080694d39bcb9aee57&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77f207fa8c71ca071a396427e788ad46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-254a838d380639a750a841f49783616f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-301a650391975642e854ed02135a0812&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9233f58a4f0f40156583723a1ef120cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e2db0657fae612abbb5778b4065cd86&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7566eaf604ece2fba223c2c887c38088&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0867a733c08a7b40fceaca6c36f02528&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc4469d9a1123a581838f093850a0ec4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-759f6d7d103fee2c466f82f605e71182&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d35bd39a02d2b483da7cfa20826b8d6e</data>
