<node id="Deponent">
  <data key="d0">Deponent</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A Deponent is an individual who provides sworn evidence or testimony under oath during a legal proceeding known as a deposition. As a witness in this context, a deponent is legally entitled to review the resulting transcript or recording of their testimony and possesses the right to make or suggest changes to the document to ensure its accuracy before it is finalized.

In the specific legal context described, the Deponent serves as the head of the supply chain for the American Colloid Company (ACC), a position held since 2020, and also functions as the plant manager at the ACC facility located in Archbold. This individual provides detailed testimony regarding the company's business operations, specifically focusing on coal requirements and consumption patterns. The testimony covers professional relationships and communications with various supplier contacts and truck drivers.

Furthermore, the Deponent's testimony addresses supply performance satisfaction and the broader contractual relationship between Fire Star and ACC. This includes documenting and discussing specific operational conflicts that have arisen between the two entities, providing a firsthand account of the business interactions and professional engagements central to the legal matter.&lt;SEP&gt;A deponent is an individual who gives out-of-court testimony during a deposition and has the right to review the transcript or recording.&lt;SEP&gt;A deponent is an individual who gives testimony under oath in a deposition and has the right to review the transcript.&lt;SEP&gt;The unnamed witness providing testimony during the deposition regarding various exhibits, communications, and the document production process.&lt;SEP&gt;The individual testifying under oath as a corporate representative during the legal deposition.&lt;SEP&gt;A deponent is an individual who gives testimony during a deposition, as listed in the word index.&lt;SEP&gt;A deponent is a witness or a party who gives testimony during a deposition and has the right to review and change the transcript or recording.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3aa6b92318a7dbc503df2e6bc0457f59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae65cbfade099063b5afa5686f54a4f1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-254a838d380639a750a841f49783616f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b286e33aaae00d921dabd7557311e090&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab822257583152b1080598f158d5ff4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1db5458af1cededb9c5054e17294a8c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-979561beed4236c6bf4cc756fe88e75e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbc582f48d3848d215a41b5506d1fc3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f6e556868aec38819b729d4931728e17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b87aa2374a79dfe9801180e61a932d0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4fa372e1e38f524f51867fb646c5473b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5104adfc9db5e929c6fe776c8ad944ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45dc6bc1d8bd9f7a1671126257459a66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21b64866580445e8fae3d73e6cbdeafa</data>
