<node id="Ms. Rathke">
  <data key="d0">Ms. Rathke</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Ms. Rathke, who is also referred to as Sarah, is a legal professional and attorney who plays a multifaceted role in litigation and deposition proceedings. She serves as both an examining attorney and defensive counsel, ensuring that legal procedures are followed and that her clients' interests are protected throughout the discovery process. Her involvement spans from the initial phases of litigation—including authoring correspondence to Tim Jones and sending draft complaints to deponents' companies—to the active management of witness testimony and evidence presentation during formal legal proceedings.

As an examining attorney, Ms. Rathke takes a lead role in conducting the questioning of various individuals, including Timothy M. Jones, Neil Miller, Mr. Warren, Mr. Wagner, and a deponent named Cotton. During these sessions, she utilizes screen-sharing technology to present and mark exhibits for identification, often identifying documents by their Bates labels to maintain an organized evidentiary record. Her questioning covers a broad spectrum of subjects, such as professional backgrounds, dedication to contract fulfillment, production reports, coal supply agreements, and coal delivery requirements. She also delves into the business impacts of environmental events like floods, force majeure claims, and specialized mining information.

In her capacity as defensive counsel, Ms. Rathke provides legal representation and guidance to witnesses, acting to preserve the integrity of their testimony and the questioning process. She frequently interacts with opposing counsel, such as Mr. Hunter, raising various formal legal objections concerning the form, foundation, scope, and clarity of questions. Her objections often address specific technicalities, including the scope of 30(b)(6) testimony, the completeness of exhibits, and the foundational basis for inquiries into specialized topics. She also facilitates witness clarity by providing necessary interjections and ensuring answers remain comprehensive and within the appropriate legal framework.

Beyond her direct legal advocacy, Ms. Rathke manages the administrative and logistical aspects of legal proceedings. This includes coordinating witness schedules, arranging procedural breaks, and overseeing the concluding details of the record. Throughout all interactions, she maintains a focus on strict adherence to procedural standards, ensuring the production of evidence and the conduct of the deposition remain consistent with legal requirements.</data>
