<node id="Case 3:22-cv-01342-JZ">
  <data key="d0">Case 3:22-cv-01342-JZ</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Case 3:22-cv-01342-JZ is a formal federal legal case identifier and civil lawsuit proceeding within the United States federal court system. The litigation involves a legal dispute between the American Colloid Company (also referred to as ACC or ACC Coal) and Fire Star Energy Resources, LLC (Fire Star). The central conflict of the case revolves around allegations of a breach of contract and specific disputes related to coal supply.

The judicial process for Case 3:22-cv-01342-JZ encompasses various discovery processes and evidentiary proceedings, including the examination of Fire Star’s business records. The official record features recorded testimonies from multiple witnesses, including depositions from individuals identified as D. Jones, Scott Warren, and Tim. To support these proceedings, the case file includes detailed transcripts, marked exhibits, certification documents, and comprehensive word indices designed to facilitate the systematic organization of the litigation.

Significant procedural milestones in Case 3:22-cv-01342-JZ are marked by specific court filings that form the official record. On January 11, 2024, several documents were filed, including Document 66-1 and Document 69-1, which provided a detailed account of depositions, transcript indices, and various proceedings. Subsequently, on July 8, 2024, further documentation was added to the record, such as Document 98-1 and materials associated with PageID 2282. These filings serve as essential components of the case, ensuring that all claims, evidence, and testimonies are accurately captured and attributed to this ongoing federal matter.</data>
