<node id="Mike">
  <data key="d0">Mike</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Mike was a former employee of a company represented by a witness in a legal proceeding, where he held the specific responsibility of monitoring coal costs and preparing initial financial calculations. His name appears extensively throughout the legal transcript index associated with the case, with references found on pages 40, 41, 88, 108, 131, 134, 143, 144, 151, 152, 155, and 156.

Professionally, Mike was a central figure in communications and operational management regarding coal shipments and the company's relationship with the supplier, Fire Star. He was the primary recipient of an email from an individual named Neil concerning this supplier relationship. Within this correspondence, Mike was the specific addressee of a paragraph explaining Fire Star's lack of knowledge regarding deliveries made to Belvidere. Records indicate that Mike misunderstood the specific arrangements and formal agreements that had been established with Fire Star concerning coal shipments.

During his tenure, Mike played a decisive role in logistical discussions and business strategy. He intervened in discussions regarding truck shipments and ultimately made the decision to cease certain business practices moving forward. His involvement in these disputes and his administrative oversight of coal-related costs are documented as key points of interest within the indexed legal transcripts.&lt;SEP&gt;Mike is an individual mentioned in the word index, distinct from the entry for Michael.&lt;SEP&gt;Mike is an individual who is frequently referenced throughout the legal transcript across numerous pages.</data>
