<node id="Exhibit 10">
  <data key="d0">Exhibit 10</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Exhibit 10 is a legal document and artifact identified as the Complaint filed by ACC against Fire Star in a court case. Used extensively as evidence during depositions, it serves as a foundational record within the proceedings. The document is characterized as a collection of correspondence and formal filings that outline the legal grievances and factual basis of the litigation between the two parties.

The contents of Exhibit 10 include a series of emails and a letter dated July 19, 2022, sent by Mr. Wagner to individuals identified as Tim and Dwayne Jones. These communications, primarily originating from June and July 2022, detail specific business operations including coal requirements and various invoices. The exhibit captures critical interactions relevant to the dispute, providing a chronological record of the professional relationship and emerging conflicts during this period.

In addition to formal letters and emails, Exhibit 10 incorporates documents or text message records marked for identification during deposition testimony. These records contain specific messages regarding the cessation of coal deliveries and information pertaining to the Chattanooga business. By synthesizing these various forms of communication, Exhibit 10 functions as a comprehensive evidentiary record used to substantiate claims made within the legal complaint.</data>
