<node id="The Witness">
  <data key="d0">The Witness</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Witness represents two distinct roles within the context of the provided legal testimony, corresponding to the two primary parties involved in a business dispute: the American Colloid Company (ACC) and Fire Star Energy.

The Witness, in one capacity, serves as the 30(b)(6) corporate designee for the American Colloid Company (ACC). This individual, potentially identified as Tim, is affiliated with the Archbold facility and possesses an extensive mechanical background. The Witness provides specialized knowledge regarding plant operations, machinery maintenance, and plant capacity, specifically concerning the Archbold and Troy facilities. In this role, the Witness manages supplier relationships and offers insight into ACC’s supply chains, distribution networks, and internal operational procedures, such as the use of Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) systems. The testimony covers coal procurement, grinding operations, inventory management, and the financial aspects of logistics, including payment procedures and the costs associated with cover coal. This Witness also details the legal grievances held by ACC against Fire Star, focusing on contract negotiations, communication protocols, and alleged contractual breaches involving coal quality and volume shortages.

The Witness is also identified as the owner and primary manager of Fire Star Energy (and its predecessor entities). This individual is the brother of Duane Jones and dedicates forty or more hours a week to the operational management of the company. This Witness provides testimony regarding the history, corporate structure, and coal mining operations of Fire Star, including coal production, brokerage, and shipping logistics. Having negotiated the coal supply agreement on behalf of Fire Star, the Witness addresses the business interactions between Fire Star and ACC, explaining the invoicing process and responding to allegations of shipment defaults.

The testimony provided by the Fire Star representative further elaborates on professional communications with figures such as Mr. Miller, Mike Wagner, and Ms. Perkins. The Witness addresses specific operational challenges, including road closures and flood events, to support force majeure claims and explain coal delivery disruptions. Throughout the deposition, the Witness reviews legal exhibits, such as contracts and text messages, and provides testimony regarding the right of first refusal, settlement negotiations, and the accuracy of prior interrogatory answers. Both iterations of the Witness serve to clarify the complex business and legal relationship between ACC and Fire Star from their respective corporate perspectives.</data>
