<node id="Wagner">
  <data key="d0">Wagner</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Wagner is an individual identified as a representative associated with ACC who played a significant role in communications and legal proceedings regarding contract requirements and financial obligations. In his professional capacity at ACC, Wagner was responsible for communicating with Fire Star concerning outstanding invoices, coal deliveries, and specific tonnage requirements. His involvement in these operational matters is documented through various forms of correspondence, including several emails he sent to address logistical issues and the resolution of unpaid balances.

A notable piece of evidence involving Wagner is a letter he authored on July 19, 2022. This correspondence was addressed to Tim and Dwayne Jones and was formally entered into the legal record as Defendant's Exhibit 10. This letter, alongside his electronic communications, highlights his active management of the business relationship and his role in articulating the contractual positions of ACC.

Within the context of the legal proceedings, Wagner is identified as a witness whose testimony and actions are documented extensively. His name and testimony are indexed throughout the legal transcript, specifically appearing on pages 40, 88, 107, 108, 129, and 161. The frequency of these citations indicates that Wagner held a central role in the proceedings, providing substantial testimony or serving as a primary figure whose actions were under scrutiny during the litigation.</data>
