<node id="Michael">
  <data key="d0">Michael</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Michael is an individual identified as a professional superior within a business and legal context, notably involved in high-level dealings with an entity called Fire Star. He was specifically tasked with striking deals and cultivating a business relationship with Fire Star, a responsibility assigned to him because the testifying witness was no longer permitted to communicate with that organization. Michael's role also included placing a significant order for coal and acting as a potential source of communication regarding delivery shortfalls.

Interpersonally, Michael maintained a tense relationship with an individual named Dwayne. This conflict eventually escalated to the point where Michael instructed Mr. Miller to cease all communication with Dwayne. Furthermore, the witness Tim indicated that he rarely speaks with Michael, suggesting a distance in their professional interaction despite Michael's superior status.

Michael's involvement in these business operations and disputes is documented extensively throughout a legal transcript. His name appears frequently in the word index, with specific mentions on pages 166 and 169, indicating that his testimony or actions were central to the legal proceedings being indexed.</data>
