<node id="Invoices">
  <data key="d0">Invoices</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Invoices are financial documents and records that facilitate and record coal purchase transactions, specifically those involving coal shipments from Chattanooga. These documents are typically submitted to corporate offices via email to ensure payment to suppliers, such as Fire Star. In the context of legal proceedings, invoices serve as essential evidence and subjects of discussion, having been reviewed by witnesses during the preparation for depositions and legal cases.

Within the operational framework of the involved companies, invoices represent amounts owed for goods received. While the system allows for efficient payment when invoices are supported by purchase orders, the witness’s company historically paid these obligations later than standard terms. Such delays are often attributed to internal system cycles and specific issues regarding the approval of surcharges. 

Invoices have also been at the center of significant commercial disruptions and legal disputes. Specifically, a nonpayment dispute between parties identified as Dwayne and ACC arose when Dwayne claimed that certain invoices remained unpaid. This failure to approve and pay invoices, particularly at the Archbold Plant, led to a halt in coal shipments and broader disruptions in product delivery. These financial records therefore serve as both a record of transaction and a primary point of contention in the recorded legal transcript.&lt;SEP&gt;Invoices are financial documents issued for payment; ACC reportedly failed to pay numerous invoices within the agreed timeframe.&lt;SEP&gt;Invoices are financial documents issued by Fire Star to ACC that trigger a 30-day payment obligation upon their receipt.&lt;SEP&gt;A series of numbered financial documents, including invoices 4978, 4997, 5008, 5018, 5035, 5045, 5057, 5069, 5076, 5090, 5014, 5119, 5140, and 5149, spanning August 2021 to May 2022 and listed as evidentiary exhibits.&lt;SEP&gt;Invoices are financial documents sent by Fire Star to ACC for payment, based on the weights recorded at the Archbold facility.&lt;SEP&gt;The financial documents representing the debt ACC owed to Tim's organization, which were central to the payment dispute.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5615da5f26bf1a4c451ff93c5d9cf990&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20985475deeff0feffae4d18b011ee8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aa66b57078d2cf7712dd3f3924568ac6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77f207fa8c71ca071a396427e788ad46&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d6d55a1b3a1206b911d641bfa5aaf53&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a2fa8d820719e1257925db86c0ebc64b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6651d4b1167389e3589940fb1cba165&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce0536f5d7fd6c2825c2025e7a85ff94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-661f83c9a8a763dd0fc15aed9cf8bab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-78e42622bccb6a56cd2ef212106aa4d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbc582f48d3848d215a41b5506d1fc3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b109525e1396d3c343edaca4b1355b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58baed9d52d175a1f6d13d75ff252edc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2028cbb4e322060dc3699f091af3659&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de14ed60023727d07befbafa5a854c60</data>
