<node id="Case: 3:22-cv-01342-JZ">
  <data key="d0">Case: 3:22-cv-01342-JZ</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Case: 3:22-cv-01342-JZ is a unique federal judicial case identifier and civil docket number assigned to a specific legal proceeding within the United States federal court system, particularly the United States District Court. Functioning as the primary designation for tracking the progress of litigation, this identifier is used to organize comprehensive court records, including legal filings, testimony, exhibits, and interrogatory answers. It serves as the structured reference for all associated documentation produced throughout the discovery and trial process, ensuring the cohesive management of evidence and legal proceedings.

The legal matter represented by Case: 3:22-cv-01342-JZ involves a civil dispute primarily between the entities ACC and Fire Star, with the additional involvement of a company associated with a witness in the proceedings. The litigation centers on a complaint filed against Fire Star regarding a dispute over coal orders and payments. A central component of the allegations is that ACC was consistently behind on its payment obligations. This case number is the official designation under which the dispute is heard and is utilized across all formal court filings to maintain clarity and context for the ongoing litigation.

Significant documentation has been filed under Case: 3:22-cv-01342-JZ, with notable filings occurring on January 11, 2024, and July 8, 2024. These records encompass deposition transcripts, detailed transcript indices, errata sheets, and various discovery documents essential to the federal civil case, such as Exhibit 71. Specific markers, such as Doc #: 66-1, Doc #: 69-1, and PageID references including 606, 961, 1191, 1192, and 2281, are used to categorize and track these filings within the court system. Veritext Legal Solutions provided the professional transcription services for the testimonies and documentation associated with the case, which are cataloged under this identifier to facilitate the legal discovery process and provide necessary litigation support services.</data>
