<node id="Federal Rules Of Civil Procedure">
  <data key="d0">Federal Rules Of Civil Procedure</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A body of rules governing civil legal proceedings in United States federal courts.&lt;SEP&gt;The Federal Rules of Civil Procedure are the set of rules that govern civil lawsuits in United States district courts.&lt;SEP&gt;The procedural rules under which the deposition of Scott Warren was conducted.&lt;SEP&gt;The Federal Rules of Civil Procedure are a set of regulations governing the conduct of civil lawsuits in United States federal courts.&lt;SEP&gt;The Federal Rules of Civil Procedure is the body of rules governing legal proceedings in United States federal courts.&lt;SEP&gt;The Federal Rules of Civil Procedure are a set of federal regulations governing legal proceedings, provided in this context for informational purposes.</data>
