<node id="Rule 30">
  <data key="d0">Rule 30</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A specific regulation within the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure that outlines the procedures for witnesses to review and modify deposition transcripts.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 30 is a specific section of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure that outlines the procedures for depositions by oral examination, including witness review and changes to transcripts.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 30 is a specific section of the Ohio Rules of Civil Procedure that outlines the procedures for submitting, reviewing, and signing deposition testimony.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 30 is a specific regulation within the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure that outlines the procedures for depositions by oral examination, including the review process by witnesses.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 30 is a specific section of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure that outlines the protocols for depositions by oral examination.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 30 is a specific section of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure that outlines the rules for conducting depositions.</data>
