<node id="Witness">
  <data key="d0">Witness</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A Witness is an individual who provides sworn testimony or evidence as part of the official legal record for a case. This role involves delivering oral testimony under oath, which is subsequently transcribed into a deposition. As a deponent, the Witness is granted specific legal rights to review the resulting transcript and make necessary changes or corrections before signing it. The significance of this role within a legal matter is often reflected by substantial page references within the document index.

In specific legal contexts, a Witness may provide testimony based on professional expertise, such as specialized knowledge of the coal industry. One such Witness is identified as the brother of Duane and is actively involved in the management and operations of a company known as Fire Star. This individual provides specific details regarding Fire Star’s business operations, facility acquisitions, and professional dealings with ACC.

Furthermore, the testimony provided by a Witness can encompass a wide range of subjects relevant to the litigation, including accounts of flood events and road closures. During the deposition or legal proceeding, the Witness is also responsible for identifying and authenticating various exhibits. Ultimately, the Witness serves as a critical source of evidence, contributing essential facts, personal observations, and professional perspectives to the legal record.</data>
