<node id="Officer">
  <data key="d0">Officer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A legal official responsible for notifying the deponent of transcript availability and documenting the review process in a certificate.&lt;SEP&gt;An Officer is a person of authority mentioned in the legal record, likely a court or law enforcement official.&lt;SEP&gt;An officer is a legal official responsible for notifying the deponent of transcript availability and certifying the deposition process, including any changes made by the deponent.&lt;SEP&gt;An officer is the official responsible for entering witness changes into a deposition and signing the record if the witness is unable or refuses to do so.&lt;SEP&gt;An individual identified by their professional rank or duty within the transcript records.&lt;SEP&gt;The officer is the official who presides over a deposition, notifies the deponent of transcript availability, and signs a certificate regarding review and changes.&lt;SEP&gt;The officer is a legal professional responsible for notifying the deponent of transcript availability and preparing a certificate noting changes or review requests.</data>
