<node id="Exhibits">
  <data key="d0">Exhibits</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Exhibits are documents, physical items, or materials submitted as evidence during legal proceedings, most notably during depositions. These items are typically introduced by attorneys or court reporters to be included as part of the official record. Once submitted, Exhibits are formally processed and verified by Veritext Legal Solutions, ensuring they are accurately integrated into the legal documentation and attached to the corresponding deposition transcript.

Within the context of legal documentation, Exhibits are frequently cited and referenced throughout the proceedings. Specific references to these items can be found on pages 3 and 4 of the transcript. Furthermore, Exhibits are documented within a formal index that provides precise location references, such as 2:6, 3:1, 4:1, 5:1, and 6:1, allowing for efficient navigation and retrieval of evidence within the case files.

Due to their significance as evidence, Exhibits are subject to rigorous handling and security protocols. They are stored under strict facility and personnel access controls to maintain the integrity and chain of custody of the documentation or physical objects. This ensures that all materials introduced during the legal process remain secure and are accessible only to authorized individuals.</data>
