<node id="Rule 30(f)(1)">
  <data key="d0">Rule 30(f)(1)</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A specific section of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure that dictates the requirements for an officer's certificate regarding deposition reviews.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 30(f)(1) is a subsection of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure that prescribes the requirements and contents of the officer's certificate in a deposition.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 30(f)(1) is a specific legal provision that prescribes the requirements for the certificate prepared by the officer following a deposition.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 30(f)(1) is a legal rule that prescribes the requirements for an officer's certificate in a deposition.</data>
