  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">A document where an officer notes whether a transcript review was requested and attaches any changes made by the deponent.&lt;SEP&gt;The Officer's Certificate is a legal document where the officer notes review requests and attaches any changes made by the deponent to the transcript.&lt;SEP&gt;The officer's certificate is a formal document, prescribed by Rule 30(f)(1), where the officer notes whether a review was requested and attaches any changes made by the deponent.&lt;SEP&gt;The officer's certificate is a document prescribed by Rule 30(f)(1) that records whether a review was requested and includes any changes made by the deponent.</data>
