<node id="Fuel Surcharge">
  <data key="d0">Fuel Surcharge</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Fuel Surcharge is a financial cost adjustment and additional fee introduced by Fire Star in March 2022. This charge was implemented in response to significant increases in fuel prices across the United States and was applied to the transport of goods and the supply of coal. While the surcharge was initially established outside of formal contract terms through an agreement with Michael Wagner, it subsequently became a subject of negotiation and contract modification. The deponent’s company implemented this price adjustment across all customer accounts, mandating it as a requirement for the continued provision of services and coal supplies.

The implementation of the Fuel Surcharge had substantial operational consequences, particularly regarding accounting and settlement procedures. Within the accounting systems of client organizations such as ACC, the fee necessitated that specific invoices, such as those identified in Exhibit 73, be processed differently than standard transactions. These specialized requirements created exceptions in invoice payment systems, which led to settlement delays and preceded inquiries into late payments. Dorothy Dreher was among the individuals responsible for discussing and managing the approval and processing of these surcharged invoices.

Beyond its technical impact on accounting, the Fuel Surcharge served as a major point of contention that strained the business relationship between Fire Star and its clients. The surcharge was a primary focus of business-related communications, including phone calls between an individual named Dwayne and his associates. It was also identified as a significant concern for organizational leadership, highlighting its role as a disruptive element in professional dealings. Ultimately, the requirement for organizations to accept the surcharge to ensure ongoing coal supplies became a central conflict in the involved parties' commercial interactions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-20985475deeff0feffae4d18b011ee8e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1acc0c2748bf5b184c2f1284638c9089&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-709ecd2e6e205eb2a4f3991b4c1aa9ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ff8ea4fb9a276eb3036f6b13650d835&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9233f58a4f0f40156583723a1ef120cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-661f83c9a8a763dd0fc15aed9cf8bab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b109525e1396d3c343edaca4b1355b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-759f6d7d103fee2c466f82f605e71182&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-872baedd657194f10bff17517ac33313&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b07c44e2ebc50b3456fe7fdf7de2bdbc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eabc48583c856796f9f0b6feb5346678&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a649e347db48560371ae468a01e05ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f348a463c6446420e2f4187560950349&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf3b2577bfe15593df5908753840d030&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f41190078a5f4d481949901834984dc7</data>
