  <data key="d2">2022 is the specific calendar year that serves as the primary temporal framework for the events, testimony, and evidence documented within the legal record. It functions as a major data category and primary heading in the document’s index, organizing a significant volume of page and line references that point to relevant testimony and evidence. This year is also the timeframe for specific communications found in Exhibit 7 and is cited by the witness as the period during which the primary events and conversations in question took place.

In terms of industrial operations, 2022 marks the period when ground coal was processed at Archbold and delivered to the Belvidere plant. During the legal deposition, this year was referenced extensively regarding plant operations, coal supply volumes, and the specific records requested for discovery. Economically, 2022 is identified as a duration during which purchased cover coal remained significantly more expensive, serving as a key time marker for analyzing the costs and logistics associated with the coal supply chain during that period.</data>
