<node id="Mr. Miller">
  <data key="d0">Mr. Miller</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Mr. Miller is a representative associated with ACC who plays a central role in the operational and logistical management of coal inventory and shipments. In his capacity at the facility, he is responsible for monitoring coal stock levels and communicating specific requirements for additional shipments to ensure continuous processing. This includes coordinating the volume of coal needed, such as a requirement he communicated on December 14, 2021, for 400 tons of coal to be delivered on a weekly basis.

His professional duties involve extensive communication with external partners and service providers. Mr. Miller has engaged with Fire Star to inquire about their capacity to provide services at ACC's Belvidere location and was carbon-copied on business emails regarding these interactions, including correspondence from Mike Wagner. He also maintains direct contact with individuals such as Dwayne, using text messaging to discuss critical operational details like payment statuses and shipping schedules. His communications often cover technical and logistical aspects, including processing needs, equipment issues, and specific requirements for the equipment and personnel utilized for hauling coal.

Beyond his day-to-day operations, Mr. Miller is involved in legal proceedings related to these business activities. He has provided testimony as a witness in a deposition, offering insights into business communications, coal production, and the interpersonal tensions surrounding the case. His involvement in these legal matters highlights his position as a key figure in documenting and overseeing the contractual and operational relationship between ACC and its contractors.&lt;SEP&gt;Mr. Miller is an individual who was copied on the email sent by Rachel Perkins.`&lt;SEP&gt;Mr. Miller is an individual mentioned during the testimony in the context of inquiries about communications regarding the right of first refusal.&lt;SEP&gt;Mr. Miller is an individual who sent an email requesting a consistent weekly supply of ground coal for several plant locations.&lt;SEP&gt;An individual who sent an email requesting coal supply for multiple facilities, a request that was subsequently denied.&lt;SEP&gt;Mr. Miller is an individual involved in the email communications documented in Exhibit 85.</data>
