<node id="Neil Miller">
  <data key="d0">Neil Miller</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Neil Miller is a professional associated with the American Colloid Company (ACC), where he has served as the plant manager of the Archbold facility for approximately five years. In this capacity, Miller is responsible for managing the plant's operational systems and communicating weekly load acceptance capacities. He possesses specialized knowledge regarding the plant's role in the company’s broader supply chain, particularly in providing ground coal to other facilities such as the Troy plant. While one description identifies him as an affiliate of Fire Star Energy Resources, LLC, the majority of records and legal documentation confirm he is an ACC employee whose interactions with Fire Star were a primary focus of corporate litigation.

In his role as plant manager, Neil Miller has been a central figure in managing relationships with coal suppliers. He frequently communicated with individuals such as Duane Jones, Mike Wagner, and Cotton Couch regarding coal requirements, tonnage needs, and the scheduling of deliveries. These communications often took an informal tone, involving frequent text messages and emails where Miller requested increased coal supplies, shared photos of storage facilities, and reported on inventory levels. For instance, in November 2021, he reported an "empty building" to emphasize the urgent need for shipments. Although he participated in high-level discussions regarding coal needs, he was reportedly restricted at one point from communicating directly with Cotton Couch, instead coordinating through Duane Jones.

Beyond operational logistics, Neil Miller was involved in the administrative and financial aspects of the supplier relationship. He was frequently copied on communications regarding significant delays in invoice payments and participated in discussions with individuals like Tim concerning the requirement for payment assurances before continuing business. While Miller was included in these payment-related email exchanges to maintain operational awareness, he did not personally process or pay the bills. He also acted as a source of information for others regarding the actions and attitudes of personnel such as Aric Wentz.

Neil Miller played a significant role in the legal matter of American Colloid Company versus Fire Star Energy Resources, LLC. His involvement is extensively documented through sworn testimony, a videotaped deposition, and various legal exhibits, including text messages and emails identified in discovery searches. He contributed his historical knowledge of plant operations to the preparation of the legal complaint and provided testimony on technical issues, such as coal quality testing and the utilization of coal in different products. Throughout the dispute, Miller was instrumental in addressing the breakdown in supply and the subsequent failures in communication between ACC and its providers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9fa03c7b0f86f656ce837c07d649fbde&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6a00a5a879b6b214e4ddee1c49d70ac7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a11202ff8b7f6ba262da062e4c328158&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-065641bb4a632b952399055a6c197f7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-890fa85548914bc59a26974a429c4e21&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a84012ee527927df3cba96bd82645063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-37bd5da834c461a6ccd2a7eb73c0210a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b8ca9890fbdff7286b7ff2a7b952323&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4eb8f03d866a8915c604a15fe987d49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f49b6e55a9d910a0c8b04633372d3d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ff8ea4fb9a276eb3036f6b13650d835&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a2fa8d820719e1257925db86c0ebc64b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7a806f0397efbdda46f27050ca5f69a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-170a31cc79e961c5f09937e57d832509&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1db5458af1cededb9c5054e17294a8c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76b142c69bd1fd0042f02d144521dea3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91ae622aa3716a4b71176bab6a4c634c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0fdeef1a7af602b992743ca983179b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7566eaf604ece2fba223c2c887c38088&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bf5b8711461b0e50ae4d1999bbc86ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d27d110d73a66d31e8d03e4b6f8b8f74&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4fdf13248aed5385075305f0203ad2b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0221087bef0e7a6186d86f99a70ffc95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f9ab40d430700b4968945f064e8400cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d699f913a8b37597b19cd0e1b1798b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58baed9d52d175a1f6d13d75ff252edc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eabc48583c856796f9f0b6feb5346678&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2028cbb4e322060dc3699f091af3659&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a649e347db48560371ae468a01e05ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5104adfc9db5e929c6fe776c8ad944ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f348a463c6446420e2f4187560950349&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47a4c64d17422cabf37987557b8d9c98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de14ed60023727d07befbafa5a854c60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2303ff741d8017a5176d75a2abdfe5ef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c04f49f2f1828e187e2d46075aba09f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-182570a48865445e060a0af61ce1cd8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe738ecfa2bfb6f1e43bab47e86f274a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-320ecdd7bc0257e71d40887d3e9b4742&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-410e248374ac5c766b1c22f0ac604a22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-29e3634a63146460c270b610b9966f0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07fe3dd18c0d67895