<node id="American Colloid Company">
  <data key="d0">American Colloid Company</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">American Colloid Company, also commonly referred to as ACC, is an industrial organization specializing in the production of foundry products and the management of foundry material supply chains. In 2014, the company was acquired by Minerals Technologies (MTI) and currently operates as a division or related entity of MTI. Its workforce includes notable employees such as Neil Barthalamue Miller and Aric Wentz. Additionally, the company’s supply chain operations were previously led by Laura Landau, who served as the head of the department prior to her retirement.

In the legal domain, American Colloid Company is the plaintiff and counter-defendant in a lawsuit designated as Case No. 3:22-cv-01342. This legal action is brought against Fire Star Energy Resources, LLC, in which American Colloid Company serves as a primary party. During the litigation process, the organization has been represented by a witness during deposition proceedings. The company is consistently identified across legal records as the central plaintiff in this dispute with Fire Star Energy Resources, LLC.</data>
