<node id="Video Operator">
  <data key="d0">Video Operator</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Video Operator is a professional technician responsible for managing and capturing the audio-visual recording of legal depositions and other official proceedings. This individual is tasked with the comprehensive management of the video recording of testimony, ensuring that all legal proceedings are documented accurately. Their core duties include operating technical recording equipment, maintaining the hardware, and performing necessary logistical tasks such as changing memory cards or other media units to ensure continuous coverage.

In addition to technical oversight, the Video Operator is responsible for monitoring the status of the record and noting the official time throughout the session. This includes tracking the record time and specifically noting the start and end times of individual media units. The operator plays a critical role in the procedural flow of the deposition by managing on-the-record and off-the-record transitions. 

The Video Operator also serves as a session monitor, announcing the official status of the recording to the participants and marking the precise start and end points of the deposition. By managing these transitions and maintaining the technical integrity of the audio-visual files, the Video Operator ensures a reliable and complete record of the testimony provided during the legal process.</data>
