<node id="Exhibit 1">
  <data key="d0">Exhibit 1</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Exhibit 1 refers to a document marked for identification and utilized as a legal exhibit during depositions and legal proceedings. It is frequently cited in the context of testimony, such as the deposition of Scott Warren, where it was identified as a subpoena or as B&amp;W Resources' formal response to a subpoena. The document serves as a foundational piece of evidence presented to witnesses to facilitate discussion and clarify specific facts within the legal record.

In several descriptions, Exhibit 1 is characterized as a data-intensive document, specifically an Excel spreadsheet or a printout from an Excel file. This version of the exhibit contains detailed charts and records documenting coal stockpile data, usage, deliveries, and coal output. During legal proceedings, this spreadsheet was used to examine and discuss inventory levels and stock totals.

Additionally, Exhibit 1 is identified as "purchase order dash one" (PO-1), a specific commercial document referenced during depositions. This purchase order is dated January 5, 2021, and specifies the delivery of 600 tons of coal from ACC to Fire Star. Whether viewed as a procedural subpoena response, a technical spreadsheet of coal inventory, or a specific purchase order, Exhibit 1 serves as a primary evidentiary tool for documenting coal-related transactions and operational data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-254a838d380639a750a841f49783616f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d6d709d0ec6b3472961b88797a09fc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f81f0f537e156601c528f2be74cc1abe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-04a825ac4b8751ff2bee5d3a5f6f56a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8791554819fb42f5afecfe547526d02e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-872baedd657194f10bff17517ac33313&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26133255971de373d8862139ecc99220&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f41879e062c3be5c70a69159a6ce804a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fff22f122484c9f576c6d89686abf9f0</data>
