<node id="Deposition">
  <data key="d0">Deposition</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A Deposition is a formal legal proceeding and event conducted during the discovery phase of a legal case, where a witness or deponent provides sworn oral testimony under oath. Governed by specific procedural rules, this pre-trial session is initiated pursuant to a formal notice and serves as a primary method for gathering evidence to be used in a court case. The testimony is meticulously recorded and transcribed by a court reporter to create an official record, a process sometimes facilitated by Veritext Legal Solutions. As a central component of the discovery process, a Deposition involves the rigorous processing of documents and testimony according to strict litigation support and production standards to ensure evidence is available for trial.

During the proceeding, attorneys question the witness on relevant matters, which frequently include business documents, contracts, market pricing, coal supply, shipments, weights, and invoices. Witnesses, such as Mr. Jones, Mr. Wagner, Mr. Cotton, and various corporate representatives, provide testimony while reviewing business exhibits and communications. Ms. Rathke is identified as a primary attorney conducting these questionings. Other individuals and entities involved in or relevant to these proceedings include Mr. Hunter and B&amp;W Resources, Inc. Specific records indicate that these legal proceedings have occurred as recently as January 11, 2024.

In legal documentation, the Deposition often serves as a primary subject, frequently indexed as a major section within the text and referenced extensively across multiple pages and lines of document indices. All sworn statements and identified exhibits are marked for the official record, ensuring that the details of the testimony remain accessible for the duration of the litigation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b286e33aaae00d921dabd7557311e090&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-301a650391975642e854ed02135a0812&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5cbe08b4b2ee1e84ea1256f73eac8634&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ab822257583152b1080598f158d5ff4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8c0c87c30bdf4b8a1daf6e93c5cd617&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b803cfdedd54225ee246885f375d88ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3a229b5af8a9e3cec23e9d269867e8b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce0536f5d7fd6c2825c2025e7a85ff94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0867a733c08a7b40fceaca6c36f02528&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-979561beed4236c6bf4cc756fe88e75e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fb4676c3f52d2f41d825a6fe4de16df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c897eacbc52ea3409f410ddbf1dd519&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9849773656bd11ce4107626d03972b64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac3fad32fec8e4d7d33ae790368a0655&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8791554819fb42f5afecfe547526d02e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b87aa2374a79dfe9801180e61a932d0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5be7ceaf649975e2f799efc4d6cae37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d699f913a8b37597b19cd0e1b1798b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eabc48583c856796f9f0b6feb5346678&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b70464475fce6ebfbef39a68f9d9e6ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-883a650c59e4458dc68f11e575383ce9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26133255971de373d8862139ecc99220&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f41190078a5f4d481949901834984dc7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-45dc6bc1d8bd9f7a1671126257459a66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe738ecfa2bfb6f1e43bab47e86f274a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8c29dc02ae5ef2a8f3e0d50f1a1f7504&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30d0b22d79b47320c1f6cc47e1d3a998&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4e5e24529707d149e3a4818e96dcbae7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07fe3dd18c0d678950b64b49cff4b258&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21b64866580445e8fae3d73e6cbdeafa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2dc9b5b950d7e245002aa75cb40b381&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f43f20395a640ee603064daae404e1d</data>
