<node id="Dwayne Jones">
  <data key="d0">Dwayne Jones</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Dwayne Jones is an individual associated with the company Fire Star, where he serves as a representative involved in the supply of coal and the management of processing plants or tipples. His professional activities include discussing business requirements, intentions, and coal supply logistics, particularly in his interactions with Neil Miller. Jones's communications regarding these matters, including various text messages, are documented in Exhibit 8.

Throughout his tenure, Dwayne Jones has been central to discussions regarding operational challenges and financial negotiations. In early 2021, he participated in phone calls and conversations concerning the impact of late payments on the timeliness of deliveries and the potential failure to provide goods. Furthermore, he acted as a point of contact for Fire Star in discussions involving quality failures and the resulting compensation requirements. 

Dwayne Jones also held specific insights into the logistical coverage of various facilities, notably maintaining an understanding that the Archbold plant was intended to cover the requirements for other plants. However, his awareness of specific business actions has been a subject of scrutiny. Along with Tim Jones, his knowledge of certain coal shipments was questioned, particularly regarding the decision to redirect coal shipments to the Belvidere plant, an action for which he was reportedly not informed.&lt;SEP&gt;Dwayne Jones is the witness being deposed whose text messages and correspondence are subject to cross-examination.&lt;SEP&gt;Dwayne Jones is a 50 percent owner and member of Fire Star Energy Resources, LLC, and the witness being deposed in the legal matter. Jones has over 30 years of experience in the coal business.&lt;SEP&gt;Dwayne Jones is an individual involved in the legal proceedings and recipient of correspondence documented in Exhibit 10.&lt;SEP&gt;Dwayne Jones is the witness whose deposition is recorded in the transcript, providing testimony regarding mining operations and communications.&lt;SEP&gt;Dwayne Jones is the witness who provided testimony in the deposition on August 17, 2023, and is responsible for reviewing the transcript and errata sheet.&lt;SEP&gt;Dwayne Jones is a witness who provided testimony, reviewed the transcript, and signed a sworn statement and an errata sheet.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-086eb781ee55d3b2985344f2c70d8bad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a84012ee527927df3cba96bd82645063&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b8ca9890fbdff7286b7ff2a7b952323&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-03a7429323501e9869beb1b87c0e9283&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf5bccaff8fd537a70e39101e74dafe1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42181ffd60d3e3b5bf175afa8698a9f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da6147e49813024d89dcb33795a793ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51f8a4880c779327848a6447b6a9410b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-82750d61ecd8735fd405d620ba554887&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-170a31cc79e961c5f09937e57d832509&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eddfd3b5802e5b17a579266c288d6819&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-661f83c9a8a763dd0fc15aed9cf8bab4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6125fc165b8564d69838c64d70084e8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b506a28447e4a2e3d78916201636374&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d54dfa73cb2af5b2e78dfb8d8d2c3d7f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9aa1016bfe3108a53a2c98b78fd57fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4793e8c6e7ff554a30b19175bfd638a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1c192ba29e37701172c6a914431b336</data>
