<node id="Jones">
  <data key="d0">Jones</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Jones is an individual who plays a central role in a legal proceeding, appearing extensively throughout the index of a legal transcript across numerous pages and lines. Referred to both individually and occasionally as part of a collective known as the Joneses, this person is a key participant in the case, functioning as a witness and deponent. The frequent references to Jones throughout the transcript suggest that their testimony and actions are fundamental to the legal matters at hand.

In a professional context, Jones is identified as a representative of Fire Star, a position that involves managing coal orders and overseeing supply logistics. Jones’s involvement in the case includes providing detailed testimony during a deposition concerning business communications and coal operations. Furthermore, Jones is documented as a recipient of correspondence from Mr. Miller, as noted in the description of Exhibit 6.

Given the volume of mentions in the legal record, Jones serves as a primary figure whose interactions and business dealings at Fire Star are central to the litigation. Their role encompasses that of a witness providing evidence on operational logistics and business communications, marking them as a significant party or witness within the legal framework of the case.</data>
