<node id="Rachel Perkins">
  <data key="d0">Rachel Perkins</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Rachel Perkins is an employee of ACC who serves as the plant administrator at the Archbold facility. In this professional capacity, Perkins acted as a primary source of information for a legal complaint, with her correspondence serving as significant evidence in the case. Her involvement is documented through various email exchanges and exhibits spanning from September 2021 to May 2022, including specific mentions in Exhibit 2 and Exhibit 11.

Perkins played a central role in the communications between the receiving company and Fire Star. She was responsible for providing detailed billing instructions and specifying the number of loads to be billed against various purchase orders. Her correspondence frequently included critical logistical data, such as delivery dates and the specific tonnage associated with purchase orders, as seen in her authorship of Exhibit 2.

Furthermore, Rachel Perkins communicated directly with a Witness via email to relay essential shipping information. These communications included providing shipping weights and destination weight data, further establishing her role in managing the data flow regarding delivery loads and billing between the involved parties. Throughout the documented period, her emails remained a key method for transmitting delivery instructions and maintaining the accuracy of shipping and billing records relevant to the legal proceedings.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37bd5da834c461a6ccd2a7eb73c0210a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5cbe08b4b2ee1e84ea1256f73eac8634&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c946e33e17040f1d499dc271e06eb652&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91ae622aa3716a4b71176bab6a4c634c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4f4d5f7cae726fcee3811fe0f307d85&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26133255971de373d8862139ecc99220&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de14ed60023727d07befbafa5a854c60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f41879e062c3be5c70a69159a6ce804a</data>
