<node id="Cover Coal">
  <data key="d0">Cover Coal</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">Cover Coal refers to the external or market-grade coal that the company ACC was compelled to purchase from alternative sources to substitute for supply that Fire Star failed to deliver. This procurement typically occurred during periods when Fire Star breached its delivery obligations or otherwise failed to meet the required supply volume. Because these purchases were made to replace missing supply, the material was often acquired at a higher market price than the original contract rate, resulting in increased costs for the company.

In addition to the financial impact, the use of Cover Coal presented significant operational challenges. In early 2022, the coal was noted to be of insufficient quality for grinding processes. The material used at the Archbold plant was specifically identified as being of lower quality, which negatively impacted the facility's performance by reducing its overall efficiency and production capacity.

Cover Coal is a central element in the company’s business documentation and legal context. It is extensively referenced across business records, internal communications, and invoices. Furthermore, it serves as a key subject in legal claims and witness testimonies, where it is used to document the material reviewed and the damages incurred due to the failure of the primary supplier.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-37bd5da834c461a6ccd2a7eb73c0210a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-868468d1edab491bb755cadee4cf1582&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-709ecd2e6e205eb2a4f3991b4c1aa9ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4eb8f03d866a8915c604a15fe987d49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42181ffd60d3e3b5bf175afa8698a9f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6651d4b1167389e3589940fb1cba165&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3802f42ea2e90df66cc37eb93f82943&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91ae622aa3716a4b71176bab6a4c634c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce0536f5d7fd6c2825c2025e7a85ff94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bf5b8711461b0e50ae4d1999bbc86ca</data>
