<node id="Purchase Orders">
  <data key="d0">Purchase Orders</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Purchase Orders are formal commercial and transactional documents used to manage business transactions, control supply levels, and ensure proper accounting within a company's system. They serve as essential records for authorizing the reception of goods and the subsequent payment for both materials and transportation services. In the specific context of coal transactions, these documents are used to manage and close out deliveries and requirements between parties, supporting efficient invoice payment and order tracking.

Within the operational framework of the involved companies, Purchase Orders are required for every delivery to validate the transaction and authorize payment within the corporate system. Specifically, in the relationship between ACC and Fire Star, these documents are issued by ACC’s accounting department. They function as financial records that Fire Star utilizes to bill for the number of loads delivered. Notably, these documents are often issued following the actual delivery of coal, reflecting a specific administrative workflow regarding how orders and deliveries are reconciled.

Beyond their day-to-day business utility, Purchase Orders serve as critical evidence in legal contexts and have been reviewed by witnesses for their relevance to ongoing disputes. They are documented as exhibits within a legal index, which includes specific procurement records such as the 263938 series (numbers 14 through 21) and the 286099 series (numbers 1 through 3). These records provide a documented history of the business transactions and supply controls maintained between the entities involved in the litigation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5cbe08b4b2ee1e84ea1256f73eac8634&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a2fa8d820719e1257925db86c0ebc64b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2dfc059d1a17532d17670f1ce88581b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91ae622aa3716a4b71176bab6a4c634c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce0536f5d7fd6c2825c2025e7a85ff94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fa96ecbf448943278b52e872cc3984a4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89fa75b320a462be370f07eb405c8186&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58baed9d52d175a1f6d13d75ff252edc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de14ed60023727d07befbafa5a854c60</data>
