<node id="Troy Plant">
  <data key="d0">Troy Plant</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The Troy Plant is an industrial manufacturing facility located in Troy, Indiana, that specializes in the production of foundry casting products. As an integral component of the ACC system, the plant maintains significant material requirements to sustain its operations, specifically requiring approximately 1,000 tons of ground coal per month.

The facility’s supply chain is closely linked to the Archbold plant, which is responsible for supplying the Troy Plant with its required ground coal products. This relationship ensures that the Troy Plant’s material coal requirements are consistently covered by Archbold's production. Documentation indicates that the facility was actively supplied with these materials during mid-2020 to meet its ongoing industrial needs.

The reliance on the Archbold plant was notably emphasized following a storage silo malfunction within the system. During this period, the Troy Plant received ground coal from the Archbold facility to compensate for the disruption and maintain its manufacturing output. The Troy Plant continues to function as a key destination for ground coal materials within its organizational network.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5e21ed3795086662478d7a51f321f88e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b8ca9890fbdff7286b7ff2a7b952323&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5cbe08b4b2ee1e84ea1256f73eac8634&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7a806f0397efbdda46f27050ca5f69a9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8fa155c99076902d5c68d436af59b4c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3802f42ea2e90df66cc37eb93f82943&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff296c565c3f4e80b9959ae67262e606&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0fdeef1a7af602b992743ca983179b0</data>
