<node id="Purchase Order">
  <data key="d0">Purchase Order</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A Purchase Order is a document used by ACC to manage material deliveries, billing, and payments, often issued to reflect or anticipate delivery quantities.&lt;SEP&gt;A purchase order is a formal document used to specify the quantity and requirements for goods to be delivered by Fire Star.&lt;SEP&gt;A purchase order is a formal business document used for transactions that is typically bypassed by Fire Star when dealing with established partners like Hazard.&lt;SEP&gt;A purchase order is a commercial document that did not govern the billing process in the described business relationship.&lt;SEP&gt;A purchase order is a document used to authorize deliveries and govern the commercial transaction between Fire Star and ACC.&lt;SEP&gt;A Purchase Order (PO) is a financial document used to authorize transactions, mentioned in the context of invoice processing and fuel surcharges.&lt;SEP&gt;A procurement request submitted by ACC for a specific quantity of product after previous debts were settled.</data>
