<node id="Mr. Wagner">
  <data key="d0">Mr. Wagner</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Mr. Wagner is an individual who served as a witness providing testimony in a legal deposition and is identified as the brother of Duane. Within his professional capacity, he appears to have held a central role in communication and coordination, as it was understood by deponents that the entity Fire Star was expected to communicate with him exclusively.

In his role, Mr. Wagner was responsible for managing and documenting coal logistics and contractual requirements. He authored various communications, including an email dated July 19, 2022, which is preserved as part of Exhibit 10. His correspondence frequently addressed coal status, shipping issues at specific locations, and dealings with various suppliers. He was also responsible for providing documentation to Aric Wentz and other representatives at ACC regarding current coal plan needs, and he regularly updated individuals named Tim and Duane on delivery requirements and contract obligations.

Mr. Wagner was also deeply involved in handling financial and payment-related disputes. On May 10, 2022, Duane escalated payment concerns to him. Mr. Wagner subsequently stated that certain shipments were being withheld specifically due to a lack of payment. His involvement in these operational matters is further evidenced by his inclusion in communications regarding the business, such as being copied on correspondence sent to Mr. Grimes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5ff8ea4fb9a276eb3036f6b13650d835&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49bb264932f821b502d0c4f28e8ee8bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-170a31cc79e961c5f09937e57d832509&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9849773656bd11ce4107626d03972b64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-62b1979b82b13aa473c9984e5d068597&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d51b6e760a730f18b43bfd8a8366573&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eabc48583c856796f9f0b6feb5346678&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a649e347db48560371ae468a01e05ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-21b64866580445e8fae3d73e6cbdeafa</data>
