<node id="Rule 30(e)">
  <data key="d0">Rule 30(e)</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Rule 30(e) is a provision within the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure that outlines the process for a witness to review and sign off on changes to a deposition transcript.&lt;SEP&gt;Rule 30(e) is a subsection of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure titled "Review By the Witness; Changes," which governs the process for witnesses to review and amend their deposition testimony.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ab822257583152b1080598f158d5ff4a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4fa372e1e38f524f51867fb646c5473b</data>
