<node id="Sulfur Content">
  <data key="d0">Sulfur Content</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A critical chemical measurement of coal; high levels are avoided to prevent surface defects in the finished products.&lt;SEP&gt;Sulfur Content is a chemical specification of coal, with specific ranges indicating the quality or type of the product.&lt;SEP&gt;Sulfur content is a quality parameter of coal; ACC requires a low sulfur level to meet its specific operational specifications.&lt;SEP&gt;Sulfur content refers to the chemical composition issue of the coal that led to the temporary suspension of deliveries from Fire Star.&lt;SEP&gt;Sulfur content is a quality specification of the product delivered by Fire Star, which was the subject of testing and dispute between ACC and Fire Star.</data>
