<node id="Lipari">
  <data key="d0">Lipari</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Lipari refers to both a commercial mining organization and an individual identified within legal documentation. As a corporate entity, Lipari is a mining company that owns and operates multiple coal mines and facilities, including the Lipari mine and the B&amp;W mine. The organization previously held ownership of the Manchester facility. Lipari serves as a primary source of coal for several customers, maintaining significant supply relationships with entities such as ACC and conducting business operations with Fire Star. The company’s mining activities and material supply to ACC were notably impacted at one point by significant flooding.

In a different context, Lipari is the name of a person documented within legal proceedings and transcript indexes. This individual is frequently referenced throughout legal testimony, particularly concerning discussions related to loads and the location of London. Due to the nature of the records, Lipari is identified as a person of interest whose name is formally cataloged in the index of the legal transcript.</data>
