<node id="London">
  <data key="d0">London</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">London is a city and small town located in Kentucky that serves as a significant geographic and operational hub within the documented legal and business proceedings. It is identified as the site of the business offices for Lipari and the organization associated with a key witness. Specifically, London is associated with the witness Scott Warren and is noted for its proximity to the offices of the various business entities involved in the case.

In addition to its role as a municipal and administrative center, London is integral to industrial and logistical operations mentioned in the testimony. It is identified as one side of the Fire Star loadout facility used for coal operations. The location is frequently cited in the context of these loadout operations and broader logistics, appearing in testimony sections particularly relevant to Lipari.

Throughout the legal documentation, London is referenced multiple times within the transcript index and is explicitly identified and marked on page 26 of the record. The town's involvement spans from its status as a location for business headquarters to its direct connection to the coal transport and facility infrastructure discussed during the proceedings.</data>
