  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The Chavies mine is a production site for low sulfur C coal that supplies various customers based on capacity and existing contract priorities.&lt;SEP&gt;Chavies mine, also known as MSHA mine number 158731, is a coal mine operated by B&amp;W Resources.&lt;SEP&gt;The Chavies mine is a coal mining facility in Kentucky operated by B&amp;W Resources, Inc.&lt;SEP&gt;A coal mining facility that experienced a shutdown and operational delays for approximately two months following a flood event.&lt;SEP&gt;The Chavies Mine is a coal mining location that experienced a shutdown due to floods in July 2022 and resumed operations on September 30, 2022.&lt;SEP&gt;The Chavies mine is a coal production site located in Kentucky that produces low sulfur C coal.</data>
