<node id="Document 66-1">
  <data key="d0">Document 66-1</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Document 66-1 is a specific legal document and evidentiary record filed on January 11, 2024, within the court proceedings of Case 3:22-cv-01342-JZ. As a formal filing recorded in the court, it serves as an attachment or exhibit that contributes to the broader legal record of the case.

The content of Document 66-1 is multi-faceted, spanning multiple pages and representing a portion of a larger 246-page record. It includes an Index of Exhibits, as well as an index of terms and references, which provide a structured overview of the submitted materials. A significant component of the document consists of a deposition transcript, specifically featuring excerpts from the deposition proceedings relevant to Case 3:22-cv-01342-JZ. Furthermore, the document incorporates relevant legal procedural rules alongside these transcript excerpts.

As a specific filing and evidentiary item, Document 66-1 functions as a transcript excerpt and a formal legal record within the judicial proceedings. It was submitted to ensure that specific deposition testimonies and related indices were officially documented and made available as part of the case’s ongoing record.</data>
