<edge source="ACC" target="The Witness">
  <data key="d7">16.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relationship between ACC and The Witness is characterized by a formal corporate representation in which The Witness serves as an employee, official corporate designee, and representative of the organization. In this capacity, The Witness provides testimony on behalf of ACC regarding its internal business operations, legal positions, and specific organizational requirements. The affiliation is marked by a strong professional identification, as The Witness utilizes collective terminology such as "us" and "our" when referring to the organization during proceedings.

Operational responsibilities held by The Witness within the ACC system include managing the plant with the organization's highest grinding capacity. Furthermore, The Witness is specifically responsible for coal procurement, a role that informs their detailed testimony concerning ACC’s internal processes and procurement strategies. This testimony is based on a comprehensive knowledge of the organization’s internal operations and official documentation.

The Witness also provides evidence regarding ACC’s external interactions and financial strategies, including its communication with Fire Star and its willingness to provide financial assurances. Regarding the history of their relationship, The Witness acknowledges a period of dispute but confirms having maintained a personal and amicable relationship with ACC prior to that time. This combination of operational expertise and representative status allows The Witness to articulate the organization's business activities and strategic interests throughout the testimony.&lt;SEP&gt;ACC contacted the Witness directly via phone or text to report that they had identified high sulfur readings.&lt;SEP&gt;The Witness conducted a search of personal communications to respond to ACC's discovery requests.&lt;SEP&gt;The Witness asserts that ACC failed to notify them regarding the RFP process for the 2023 business, despite their known intent to rebid.</data>
  <data key="d9">affiliation,business grievance,capacity leadership,communication,corporate representation,designee,dispute resolution,employment,identification,lack of notice,legal discovery,personal history,professional relationship,professional representation,professional testimony,representation,search,testimony</data>
