<edge source="Troy" target="Archbold">
  <data key="d7">8.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relationship between Archbold and Troy is defined by Archbold’s role as a contingent supplier and service provider for the Troy plant. Archbold is responsible for managing and supplying the coal requirements of the Troy facility, specifically serving as a gap filler when Troy’s own supply or processing capabilities are interrupted. This support includes providing specialized coal grinding services on an irregular, as-needed basis, particularly during mechanical breakdowns or other operational disruptions at the Troy site.

Historical records indicate that Archbold ground and supplied coal to the Troy plant in 2022, a period during which Troy’s operations were significantly interrupted. The volume of coal tonnage required from Archbold is directly linked to the operational status of the Troy facility; when Troy resumes its full internal operations and processing, the coal tonnage requirements fulfilled by Archbold are significantly reduced. Consequently, Troy is categorized as one of the primary plants whose coverage and supply needs are managed by Archbold during periods of processing instability.</data>
  <data key="d9">ad hoc service,coal distribution,contingent supply,emergency support,gap filler,grinding,industrial operations,operational dependency,operational support,ownership,resource distribution,resource sharing,supply,supply chain,supply logistics,supply planning</data>
