<edge source="Neil" target="Fire Star">
  <data key="d7">9.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relationship between Fire Star and Neil is defined by Neil’s role in managing and coordinating coal shipments for ACC. As the individual responsible for this primary supplier relationship, Neil facilitates coal deliveries by communicating inbound orders from ACC directly to the personnel at Fire Star. He is specifically tasked with arranging additional coal shipments whenever they are required to meet operational needs.

In his efforts to secure coal for ACC, Neil utilizes non-owner connections and personal relationships with contacts at Fire Star. However, his management of these shipments has been characterized by a lack of transparency toward the supplier's formal leadership. Neil has previously arranged for the redirection of coal shipments without informing Fire Star or its representatives, and he asserted in various communications that Fire Star was unaware that its coal was being supplied to the Belvidere plant.

The connection between Fire Star and Neil also involves the resolution of administrative and financial friction. Representatives from Fire Star have actively communicated their grievances to Neil, specifically complaining about a persistent and "never-ending" issue regarding late payments for the coal provided. Despite these conflicts, Neil remains the central figure responsible for navigating the logistics and maintaining the functional supply chain between the two entities.&lt;SEP&gt;Neil was reportedly instructed not to communicate with representatives from Fire Star, leading to a change in personnel contact.</data>
  <data key="d9">business communication,business relationship,communication,communication restriction,complaints,conflict,coordination,knowledge,lack of communication,logistical decisions,logistics,personal connections,procurement,relationship management,supply chain,supply coordination</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-3aa6b92318a7dbc503df2e6bc0457f59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf5bccaff8fd537a70e39101e74dafe1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42181ffd60d3e3b5bf175afa8698a9f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-607b59165140de6bdf4da7d9031e9ef0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da6147e49813024d89dcb33795a793ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51f8a4880c779327848a6447b6a9410b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5e9f4d391d8e15587e7605c40c26d0a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbc582f48d3848d215a41b5506d1fc3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f41879e062c3be5c70a69159a6ce804a</data>
  <data key="d11">Deposition by Defendant -- Neil Miller (Manager at Plaintiff) -- April 14, 2023, 1316.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;Deposition by Defendant -- Aric Wentz (Supervisor at Plaintiff) -- April 14, 2023, 0859.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;Deposition by Plaintiff -- Dwayne Jones (Owner of Defendant) -- August 17, 2023, 1101.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;Deposition by Plaintiff -- Timothy Jones (Owner of Defendant) -- July 17, 2023, 0938.pdf</data>
  <data key="d12">1777299310</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
