<edge source="Fire Star" target="Archbold">
  <data key="d7">11.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relationship between Archbold and Fire Star is primarily characterized by a supplier-purchaser agreement in which Fire Star provides raw coal to the Archbold facility. In this capacity, Fire Star sells coal on a delivered basis to fulfill the plant's specific grinding requirements and satisfies the coal needs of both the Archbold location and other associated plants. The supply arrangement is governed by a requirements contract, reflecting a formal business commitment between the two entities.

Operationally, Fire Star facilitates the transport of coal shipments, which are routed through the Archbold location. Throughout this partnership, Fire Star has maintained an awareness of the variable coal needs of the Archbold facility, adjusting its supplies to meet fluctuating manufacturing demands. The plant at Archbold serves as both a recipient of these materials and a logistical point for the distribution of coal shipments provided by Fire Star.

Currently, the contractual relationship between Archbold and Fire Star is the subject of litigation. This legal dispute centers on the requirements contract that established the terms for the sale and delivery of coal, marking a point of conflict within their established commercial interaction.&lt;SEP&gt;Fire Star provides coal to the Archbold location, with deliveries made exclusively by truck.&lt;SEP&gt;Fire Star fulfills coal orders and manages haul rates for shipments to Archbold.&lt;SEP&gt;The questioning explores whether Fire Star made additional business proposals to Archbold after July 2021.</data>
  <data key="d9">business awareness,business operations,business pitch,business relationship,commercial relationship,contractual agreement,delivered basis,delivery,legal dispute,location,logistics,procurement,shipment,supply,supply chain,supply logistics,supply relationship</data>
