</edge>
<edge source="Coal" target="End-of-the-Week Report">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The End-of-the-Week Report serves as the record for the missing coal deliveries over a four-week period.</data>
  <data key="d9">documentation,supply shortage</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-ea56e06fa48990cb993a7e9f44e99a73</data>
  <data key="d11">Deposition by Defendant -- Neil Miller (Manager at Plaintiff) -- April 14, 2023, 1316.pdf</data>
  <data key="d12">1777295725</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Coal" target="Archbold Plant">
  <data key="d7">7.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The Archbold plant is responsible for grinding and processing coal.&lt;SEP&gt;The Archbold Plant uses coal as a ground ingredient in its casting production process.&lt;SEP&gt;The Archbold plant grinds and processes between 15,000 and 20,000 tons of coal annually.&lt;SEP&gt;Coal was provided to the Archbold Plant during the period when quality issues were being addressed.&lt;SEP&gt;The movement of coal to the Archbold plant via barge or train requires specific quantity commitments in contracts compared to truck deliveries.&lt;SEP&gt;The Archbold Plant processes and grinds coal for its own use and for other affiliated plants.&lt;SEP&gt;The Archbold Plant required coal shipments for its grinding needs.</data>
