<edge source="Ms. Rathke" target="Deposition">
  <data key="d7">9.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relationship between the Deposition and Ms. Rathke is defined by her central role as the legal professional responsible for leading the proceedings. Ms. Rathke serves as the attorney conducting the formal questioning and examination of the witness or deponent. As the primary examiner, she is tasked with directing the legal inquiry and eliciting testimony through a structured interrogation process.

In addition to her role as the examiner, Ms. Rathke is a participating attorney who oversees the procedural integrity of the deposition. Her involvement includes raising procedural objections and managing the technical aspects of the questioning phase. By leading the examination and ensuring the legal standards of the session are met, Ms. Rathke acts as the principal figure responsible for the testimony gathered during the deposition.</data>
  <data key="d9">examination,legal examination,legal participation,legal proceeding,legal questioning,legal role,procedural participation,questioning</data>
