<edge source="The Witness" target="Neil Miller">
  <data key="d7">10.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relationship between Neil Miller and The Witness is characterized as a long-standing, informal, and "non-literal" business association. This professional connection served as a primary conduit for The Witness to acquire historical context and operational knowledge regarding specific corporate activities. Their interactions were foundational to The Witness’s understanding of the business landscape, particularly concerning the historical practices at the Archbold plant.

Through frequent conversations and professional interactions, The Witness received detailed historical information from Neil Miller about plant operations and the breakdown of the supply process. These discussions included explanations of how supply requirements were communicated within the organization. Furthermore, Neil Miller provided The Witness with critical insights into the fifteen-year relationship between the companies ACC and Fire Star, which informed The Witness’s perspective on long-term business dynamics.

In a legal context, The Witness consulted extensively with Neil Miller as part of the preparation process for a deposition. The Witness relies on the information gleaned from these discussions to explain business intents and historical practices. Ultimately, the testimony provided by The Witness regarding business intent and operational history is rooted in the information and professional insights gained through their relationship with Neil Miller.&lt;SEP&gt;The Witness has met Neil Miller once in a professional capacity.&lt;SEP&gt;The Witness interacted with Neil Miller and searched for text messages exchanged with him.</data>
  <data key="d9">Information Sharing,Professional Collaboration,business relationship,business understanding,communication,communication style,consultation,discussion,information sharing,information source,preparation,professional acquaintance,professional interaction,professional relationship,verification,work relationship</data>
