<edge source="The Witness" target="Mike Wagner">
  <data key="d7">10.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relationship between Mike Wagner and the Witness is characterized by a professional association primarily centered on the coal industry and plant operations. Mike Wagner serves as a representative for ACC, and the Witness was explicitly instructed that all operational communications should be directed through him. Despite the frequency of their professional interactions, the Witness has noted that they have never met Mike Wagner in person, though they were able to identify him as the ACC representative who visited Fire Star Facilities.

Communication between the two parties has been conducted through various channels, including email, text messages, and telephone calls. Mike Wagner utilized these methods to inform the Witness of his new place of employment and to discuss matters such as mitigation potential and general plant operations. Wagner also reached out to the Witness to inquire about coal shipping prices and the logistical feasibility of delivering coal to various plants.

The Witness engaged with Mike Wagner on several critical business matters, including discussions regarding rising fuel costs and requests for surcharges on haul rates. Their interactions also involved formal contractual notifications; during a phone call in June, the Witness informed Wagner of the intent to exercise the right of first refusal for business in 2023. Furthermore, the Witness provided a verbal notification to Mike Wagner stating that ACC was in default of their existing agreement. Throughout these exchanges, the Witness maintained a consistent stream of communication with Wagner via email and text regarding the ongoing coal business.</data>
  <data key="d9">business communication,communication,email correspondence,identification,negotiation,notice of default,observation,phone call,point of contact,pricing inquiry,professional communication,professional directives,text messaging,work relationship</data>
